NEET#,#NEET Living Machines - Immunoengineering#,#NEET Living Machines Thread - Immunoengineering Track#,#NEET Certificate in Living Machines - Immunoengineering Thread#,#url=https://neet.mit.edu/threads/lm
Living Machines (LM) allows you to apply engineering principles and concepts to problems in the Life and Medical Sciences, through various biotechnology innovations. As a Living Machines scholar, you have the opportunity to work on projects spanning synthetic biology, immuno-engineering, tissue engineering, microfluidics, and computational biology and other disruptive research areas, united by a theme of improving our understanding of and therapies for human disease.

subjects

immersion

growth


%% Variable declarations

idr := ""Intellectual Diversity Requirement (IDR)""{>=1}
int := ""Internship""{>=1}
thesis := ""Senior Thesis""{=15u}

urop := "UROP (credit/paid)""{>=1}
subjects, "Subjects" := 20.051,20.230,20.365,idr
immersion, "Immersion" := (20.054,urop)/int/thesis

lm_act := ""LM Activities (60 HEQ)""{>=60u}
sem := ""Seminars""{>=8}
growth, "Growth" := lm_act, sem